  "prompt": "What resorts in Renuka Lake Tourist-spots would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "While there are no specific resorts in Renuka Lake Tourist-spots explicitly advertised as safe for unmarried couples, many resorts and hotels in tourist areas across India tend to be more accommodating. The key to ensuring a hassle-free stay is to choose reputable, well-reviewed establishments and to follow certain tips:\n\n1. **Book Reputable Hotels**: Look for hotels or resorts with good reviews on platforms like TripAdvisor, Booking.com, or Google Reviews. Established chains or well-known local hotels are generally more professional and less likely to harass guests.\n\n2. **Carry Valid ID Proofs**: Always carry government-issued ID proofs for both individuals. This is not just a legal requirement but also helps in avoiding any issues during check-in.\n\n3. **Respect Local Customs**: Being respectful and discreet about your relationship can sometimes help avoid unwanted attention. \n\n4. **Avoid Public Displays of Affection**: While at the resort or in public areas, avoiding overly affectionate behavior can help avoid drawing unnecessary attention.\n\n5. **Contact the Hotel Directly**: Before booking, call the hotel directly to inquire about their policies regarding unmarried couples. Most reputable hotels will be forthcoming with this information.\n\n6. **Read Reviews Carefully**: Pay special attention to reviews from other couples, especially unmarried ones, to see if they faced any issues.\n\nHere are a few suggestions based on general reputation and reviews:\n\n1. **Renuka Ji Tourist Complex**: A government-run establishment known for its scenic beauty and good service.\n2. **Hotel Renuka**: Another local option that has garnered positive reviews for its hospitality and location.\n\nAlways remember that the experience can vary, so being prepared and choosing wisely is crucial.",
